metadata.name: Ensconced Orb #12
metadata.description:
Random cords in a circle exit at both ends at a random angle between the tangent and the normal.

Variations include colour, circle size and line quantities.

These make me think of celestial bodies or a orb ensconced in plush velvet.

metadata.name: Sun #29
metadata.description:
Sun has emerged through many many tests to emphasize contrasts. One of those tests has generated some kind of star pattern with a halo of high brightness and a more chaotic and constrasted surface. A reminiscent light in the very center and a background made of projecting brightness have also appeared during the creating process. In fact, it was even more close to the beginning of the imploding step of a star than its daily life !

Then, playing around with randomness, I have discovered that there was a large panel of possibilities going from the early stage of the implosion to the black hole occurence. Adding colors palettes and deformations have led to a complete project.

I hope you will enjoy those pieces as much as me !

metadata.name: Paper Planes #247
metadata.description:
The joys of childhood are too easily forgotten. Paper Planes is a generative art collection celebrating the joy and magic of origami: from the simplest materials spring delightful forms brimming with ingenuity.

In homage to the handicraft of paper folding, we developed a collection of four pens each with a unique hand-drawn feel: Ink, Pencil, Gel and Dip. They ensure each of our ten origami birds are sketched with subtle imperfections.

Many of the birds are folded from patterned paper based on three traditional Japanese patterns: Seigaiha, Kōjitsunagi and Shippō. Other birds are crafted from block coloured paper which provides pop and contrast whilst sometimes birds match their background, accentuating the hand-drawn strokes that sketched them.

A range of layouts bring each mint to life. Birds can flock and fly across the page. They can be confined to a regimented grid or they can escape and embrace the chaos of the currents. Contrasting frames and borders highlight different colours within each of the 15 handcrafted palettes.

If you're feeling mischievous you can press 'C' in live view to ruffle some feathers…

https://www.phaust.art/paper-planes

----------

In live view, press 'S' to save a high resolution download or add '&size=#' to the end of the URL to render at a custom height.

Original artwork by Phaust. Spring 2022. London / Brighton. Made with p5js.

metadata.name: Extreme Ways #261
metadata.description:
« Extreme ways are back again
Extreme places I didn't know
I broke everything new again
Everything that I'd owned
I threw it out the windows, came along
Extreme ways I know move apart The colors of my sea
Perfect color me… »
Song/Lyrics by Moby

All pieces are broken again and again…

Controls
Extreme ways contains some interactivity if you wish to explore.
Since this artwork is complex it takes time to draw, be patient. 

Press h in live mode to list the possibilities and see tips for interactivity usage.
Key ’s’  : Save an image of the output at the current resolution
Key 1-9 : Change resolution
Key ‘c’ : Change colors
Key ‘m’ : Change main style
Key ‘d’ : Change drawing style
…
 

Pricing
Proposed as a Dutch Auction 11-9-7-5 tez with a step every 10 minutes.


Features

I do not think rarity will be a good indicator of the quality of the output.
Trust your taste and buy on the secondary what you like…

metadata.name: Chord Unknown #157
metadata.description:
The feeling of experimenting with an instrument you have not learned, and then suddenly striking an actual chord.

The code creates several grids and then applies one of six unique deformation techniques with varying intensity. It's a defined process of experimentation, and even though I'm the one that wrote the rules, each output breaks through somehow as a complete surprise to me. So when I see them, I get a Chord Unknown.

Created by Eric Davidson. 2022.

metadata.name: Hashed Cities #56
metadata.description:
This token generates a deterministic set of minimal, abstract buildings of varying widths, heights, transparencies, and patterns, assembling a skyline view of your own unique imaginary city. Each city comes with its own randomized city day.

Each mint has a native setting (Day or Night) which combined with the current time of viewing influences real-time movements of celestial bodies in your mint, e.g. on a mint with the Day setting, the sun will only appear when viewed during the day. The piece will re-render every minute.

The individual strokes of this token feature some of my latest developments of an algorithm that generatively simulates the texture of print imperfections. They are randomized at each render to give it a unique character. Note that depending on the complexity of each mint, some renders may introduce a brief pause. The aesthetics are greatly inspired by plotter art of early computer artists such as 'City Painting' by Grace C. Hertlein.

Made in p5js
Created Nov 2021
Artist: @Yazid

metadata.name: Elswhere #221
metadata.description:
Perlin noise walks into a Julia set and finds itself Elswhere. X is real, Y is imaginary, or is it the other way around? 

Elswhere is a unique generative art series in which noise and fractal math are combined to create whimsical shapes and motifs, with an infinite number of variations. Made with p5js.

For each pixel, the noise values corresponding to the X and Y coordinates are computed and then used as the real and imaginary components for initializing a Julia set recursion. The pixel is colored based on the number of steps it takes for the recursion to reach its base case.

Keyboard controls:
[S] Save the current view.
[2] Render 2000x3000px image.
[4] Render 4000x6000px image.
[6] Render 6000x9000px image.

Created by Elsif, 2022.05

metadata.name: illusions #22
metadata.description:
"illusions" is an experiment with textures made from grains, flows and noise, which slowly forms into an abstract figure. 
It can resemble clouds, nebulae, waterfalls, neon bars and anything else your brain can imagine while looking at it.

The growth and formation patterns of "illusions" are 3:
They can grow in the form of a cloud, in the form of lines/squares or just a noise, and also in a glitch effect.

There are 11 color palettes and one of them is monochromatic in black/white, it is the rarest as there is only 4% chance of happening.

You can open the live view to have a better experience.
-Also in live view you can press the "s" key to save a .png file of the artwork.

Works properly on Chrome.

This is an artwork in p5.js.



Omar Lobato Neto, 10/03/2022
